Program: Outlook
Title: 09/11/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p004t62q
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 10 Nov 2009
Personal stories behind the news from all over the world. With Matthew Bannister. Al Gore on his crusade to save the planet, 89 Squares, Cuban Blogger Yoani Sanchez. Al Gore Former US Vice President Al Gore tells Matthew Bannister about his latest book "Our Choice" which focusses on potential solutions to the climate change issue. He also talks about his own personal journey and how he coped with losing the US Presidential election of 2000 by devoting his life to saving the planet. 89 Squares Twenty years after the fall of the Berlin wall we are hearing from people this week who were present in the various city squares across Eastern Europe - demonstrating and in some cases celebrating. Today we hear from some of those who were present in Wenceslas Square in Prague at the start of the Velvet Revolution. Cuban Blogger Award winning blogger Yoani Sanchez tells Matthew Bannister how she manages to continue blogging in Havana, despite various attempts to put her off. Show less